item.title: By: Julianne
item.dc:creator: Julianne
item.description: Hmmm I think my jr high- junior years of school I dressed really weird. I don't think my makeup was ever too bad, but I wore my docs with anything, and sometimes mixed their colors, a red on one foot, green on the other. when i got my 20 eyes and grip fasts, my skirts and dresses just got shorter, and more into the black side. I once or twice wore checkered tights with a checkered skirt, or a floppy hat that just looked like grass took a shit on my head. Omg! I wore a tiara, and sometimes cat ears. Shoot I can't believe I went in to study fashion design. I still think I may have some crazy mental fashion quirks but no way like I used to.

item.title: By: muddgirl
item.dc:creator: muddgirl
item.description:
Getting "cheap" manicures at random storefronts that only last about 5 minutes, and being too lazy to fix them myself.
Way-too-dark foundation was a big one for me, especially since I'm like one stage lighter than Ivory. I thought I could just match my cheek color and call it a day.
